<h2 id="publish-those-fonts">Publish those Fonts! <a class="headerlink" href="publishing-fonts#publish-those-fonts" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>Next, add a new task called <code>fonts</code>. The job of this guy will be to "publish"
any fonts that we have into <code>web/</code>. Right now, it's just the FontAwesome
stuff. Use the <code>app.copy()</code> and for the path, start with <code>config.bowerDir</code>.
I'll scroll up so we can see the path. Now, <code>font-awesome/fonts/*</code> to grab
everything. For the target, just <code>web/fonts</code>:</p>
